Numerical Integration Using Midpoint Rule
Project Overview
This project demonstrates the application of the Midpoint Rule to approximate the value of a definite integral and compare the result with the exact integral value. The calculations were performed using Microsoft Excel by dividing the integration interval into equal subintervals, determining midpoint values, evaluating the function, and estimating the integral numerically.
The project highlights how numerical methods can be used to solve integration problems and evaluate the accuracy of approximations by comparing them with exact solutions.

